data.text:
#106776 by lewy

Dodge DN5 700 engines was created by lewy

Hello Everyone,

I am interested in a DN5 700 series Dodge thats been offered to me and have been told it had a Cummins v504 engine from factory, how good are these and what are parts like to get.

Can anyone tell me what diesels these had in them from new.

Ive seen a Dodge with a GM fitted, was this a factory option along with the V8 Cummins.

Any help will be much appreciated.

Cheers

Lewy

Please Log in to join the conversation.

Replied by v8 inter nut on topic Re: Dodge DN5 700 engines

#106778 by bigcam

Replied by bigcam on topic Re: Dodge DN5 700 engines

Lewy, I've seen them with V504 (V8 210) as well as 6V53's, that was about it as far as diesels went I think. Both were from the factory, pretty sure I've got pictures of one with a V8 210 in it as well as 6V53.

Biggest dillema with the Cummins is electrolisys, make sure it's got inhibitor in it or leave it where it is.

The AT4's had the V8 185, 160 Cummins, and 6V53's.
